(1609, 202, 'about', 'On a boat ride through the jungle, former executive, hard-core traveler, Brazilian entrepreneur Marcia Kemp, fell in love with Peruvian Amazon – where she met a group of women.\r\nThey had amazing skills with natural fibers, and built their own grab bags, as well as super colorful accessories.\r\nOften they described themselves as Nannacay, which translated to “Hermandad de Mujeres” – SISTERHOOD.\r\nThe Sisterhood feeling is stronger than ever, and we felt it was time to portray some of the Nannacay gatherings in our Campaign.\r\n\r\nHere is SISTERHOOD, our 2017 Resort Campaign.'),
